    <text type="letter">
        <body>
            <pb xml:id="leaf001r" facs="loc.01824.001_large.jpg" type="recto"/>
            <opener>
                <dateline><name type="place">Williamson Wayne, Co. N.Y.</name><date
                        when="1865-08-06">Aug 6<hi rend="superscript">th</hi></date></dateline>
                <salute><unclear reason="illegible" cert="low" resp="#nnk">Walt</unclear>
                    dear</salute>
            </opener>

            <p><gap reason="illegible" extent="two words" unit="chars" quantity="11"/> son Alfred we
                received a letter last night <gap reason="illegible" extent="one word" unit="chars"
                    quantity="7"/> you and was pained to hear that <choice>
                    <sic>wore</sic>
                    <corr>were</corr>
                </choice> sick in the <gap reason="illegible" extent="one word" unit="chars"
                    quantity="11"/> in a <choice>
                    <sic>faren</sic>
                    <corr>foreign</corr>
                </choice> and among strangers, oh if <gap reason="illegible" extent="one word"
                    unit="chars" quantity="5"/> and your Mother could be there to take care of you
                it would be some consolation, but you said you were better <gap reason="illegible"
                    extent="one word" unit="chars" quantity="5"/> did not say what your complaint
                was we hope for the best it may be when you get this you will be well but if not
                write in <choice>
                    <sic>hast</sic>
                    <corr>haste</corr>
                </choice> or get some <gap reason="illegible" extent="one word" unit="chars"
                    quantity="4"/> to write <gap reason="illegible" extent="one word" unit="chars"
                    quantity="4"/> the particulars. we are all well at the time the weather is <gap
                    reason="illegible" extent="one word" unit="chars" quantity="6"/> and <unclear
                    reason="illegible" cert="low" resp="#nnk">very</unclear> warm. we have <gap
                    reason="illegible" extent="one word" unit="chars" quantity="8"/> planting and
                sowing <pb xml:id="leaf001v" facs="loc.01824.002_large.jpg" type="verso"/> I sowed
                    <gap reason="illegible" extent="one word" unit="chars" quantity="4"/> on the
                    <gap reason="illegible" extent="one word" unit="chars" quantity="8"/> north of
                the barn and that <gap reason="illegible" extent="one word" unit="chars"
                    quantity="5"/> too nowhere <gap reason="illegible" extent="one word"
                    unit="chars" quantity="3"/> had <gap reason="illegible" extent="one word"
                    unit="chars" quantity="8"/> year <gap reason="illegible" extent="one word"
                    unit="chars" quantity="5"/> the <gap reason="illegible" extent="two words"
                    unit="chars" quantity="12"/> road all sowed to <gap reason="illegible"
                    extent="one word" unit="chars" quantity="5"/> and we plant from <gap
                    reason="illegible" extent="one word" unit="chars" quantity="8"/> tot he ditch
                about <gap reason="illegible" extent="one word" unit="chars" quantity="8"/> 3 acres
                down north <gap reason="illegible" extent="one word" unit="chars" quantity="8"/>
                <choice>
                    <sic>ploued</sic>
                    <corr>plowed</corr>
                </choice> I have set one hundred apple trees there and 72 grape vines. <gap
                    reason="illegible" extent="one word" unit="chars" quantity="6"/> and <gap
                    reason="illegible" extent="one word" unit="chars" quantity="6"/> the plowing
                they make good <gap reason="illegible" extent="one word" unit="chars" quantity="5"
                />. I don't think of much to <gap reason="illegible" extent="two words" unit="chars"
                    quantity="13"/> the best you can and come home the first opportunity </p>
            <p><choice>
                    <sic>rite</sic>
                    <corr>write</corr>
                </choice> soon without fail and <choice>
                    <sic>rite</sic>
                    <corr>write</corr>
                </choice> if you want me <gap reason="illegible" extent="one word" unit="chars"
                    quantity="6"/> you anything and by, B.S.</p>
            <closer>
                <signed>John B. Pratt</signed>
            </closer>
            <postscript>
                <p>Williamson<lb/>Wayne Co. N Y</p>
            </postscript>
        </body>
